\b 1. Introduction\b0\line
The Digital Certificate Verification System is a console-based Java application that verifies the authenticity of digital certificates issued by educational institutions, companies, and government organizations. The system follows the DAO (Data Access Object) pattern and uses JDBC with MySQL to manage data securely.\line
\line
Traditionally, certificate verification is performed manually by checking physical documents, which is time-consuming, prone to human error, and vulnerable to forgery. This project automates the verification process using unique certificate IDs (which can be encoded as QR codes) stored in a secure database. Administrators can add, update, delete, and verify certificates through a text-based interface.\line
\page
\b 2. Objective of the Project\b0\line
- To prevent certificate forgery by maintaining a secure, central repository of issued certificates.\line
- To provide fast and reliable verification of digital certificates using a unique certificate ID or QR code content.\line
- To enable authorized administrators to register, log in, and manage certificates.\line
- To demonstrate layered software design using the DAO pattern, separating presentation, business logic, and data access.\line
- To provide a reference console application that can later be extended to a full web-based system.\line
\page
\b 3. Scope of the Project\b0\line
The scope of this project includes:\line
- A Java 17 console application with menu-driven navigation.\line
- User authentication (admin login and registration).\line
- Certificate management: add, view, search, update, and delete certificates.\line
- Certificate verification using certificate ID.\line
- MySQL database for secure storage of users and certificates.\line
- Use of DAO pattern to abstract database operations and allow easy future changes.\line
\line
Out of scope for this version:\line
- Real QR code scanning (ID is manually typed).\line
- Web UI.\line
- Advanced role management.\line
- Full-field encryption of all data.\line
\page
