- Verification requires physical presence or sharing scanned copies.\line
- The process is slow, labor-intensive, and not centralized.\line
- There is a high risk of forgery and duplication.\line
\page
\b 6. Proposed System\b0\line
The proposed Digital Certificate Verification System:\line
- Stores all issued certificates in a central database with a unique certificate ID.\line
- Allows administrators to register, log in, and manage certificates via console.\line
- Provides instant verification by entering the certificate ID.\line
- Uses statuses such as ACTIVE, EXPIRED, and REVOKED.\line
- Can be extended to web and QR-based verification in the future.\line
